# F.Y.N Timing OS Hardening Walkthrough

## 1. System Stability (P0 Fixes)

Following the comprehensive code review, we implemented several critical optimizations to ensure production stability and performance.

### Notification Error Boundary
- **Problem**: A single failed event processing in the Pub/Sub subscriber could crash the entire notification service.
- **Fix**: Wrapped the subscriber callback in a `try-catch` block with structured logging. Failed events are logged and the subscriber remains active for subsequent events.

### Allergy Crosscheck N+1 Fix
- **Problem**: [getSafeMenuItems](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/src/modules/safety/allergyCrosscheck.service.ts#118-139) was fetching ingredients one-by-one, causing $O(N)$ database round-trips.
- **Fix**: Implemented [getMenuItemsIngredientsBatch](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/src/modules/menu/menu.service.ts#256-295) in [menu.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/src/modules/menu/menu.service.ts) to fetch all data in a single SQL query.
- **Match Improvement**: Switched to word-boundary Regex (`\bword\b`) for allergen matching to prevent false positives.

### Server Infrastucture
- **Global Error Handler**: Standardized unhandled error responses to return JSON, mapping [StandardError](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/src/core/errors/StandardError.ts#42-78) codes.
- **404 Handler**: Added a catch-all route for unmapped endpoints.
- **Log Standardization**: Replaced all remaining `console.log` statements with structured `systemLogger`.

## 2. Infrastructure & Logic (P1-P3 Hardening)

### Database & Pub/Sub
- **Throughput**: Increased PostgreSQL connection pool `max` to **50** for production concurrency.
- **Health Checks**: Pub/Sub availability is now monitored via the `/health-connectors` endpoint.
- **Referential Integrity**: Added hard validation in [ar.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/src/modules/ar/ar.service.ts) to ensure `tableId` existence before anchor creation.

### Modular Architecture
- **Notification Strategy Pattern**: Refactored the [handleIncomingEvent](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/src/modules/notification/notification.service.ts#100-124) logic into a pluggable Strategy Pattern. This separates POS, Table, Inventory, and Reservation notification logic into dedicated classes.
- **State Machine Integration**: Implemented a transition-validation layer in [table.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/src/modules/table/table.service.ts) to prevent invalid status jumps (e.g., bypassing cleaning).

### Developer Experience
- **OpenAPI Spec**: Initialized [docs/openapi.yaml](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/docs/openapi.yaml) for standardized API documentation.
- **Test Stabilization**: Updated [config.ts](file:///c:/Users/henry/OneDrive/Apps/F.Y.N%201.3.26/src/core/config.ts) to support default values in `dev/test` environments, enabling the test suite to execute without failing on missing secrets.

